    <subfield code="a">The polarization operator is investigated at arbitrary photon energy in a constant and homogeneous electric field of the strength E . When the photon energy is less than the vacuum energy <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mrow><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant="italic">eE</mi><mi>ℏ</mi><mo>/</mo><mi mathvariant="italic">mc</mi></mrow></math> , the found probability describes the absorption of a soft photon by virtual electron and positron in an electric field. At this energy, the main contribution to the probability gives the process of the absorption of a soft photon by real electron and positron produced by an electric field.</subfield>
